Database migrations for the spend-tracking service using Alembic.

## Usage

Run migrations:
    DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..." make migrate

Create a new migration:
    make migrate-new name="description"

Use --rev-id for sequential numbering:
    poetry run alembic revision --rev-id 002 -m "description"

## Notes

- DATABASE_URL must be set as an environment variable
- Migrations use raw SQL (no SQLAlchemy ORM models)
- File naming uses sequential IDs: 001_initial_schema.py, 002_..., etc.
